{"title_page": "Cavan Intermediate Football Championship", "text_new": "{{Infobox GAA tournament\n| name                 = Cavan Intermediate Football Championship\n| currentlyrunning     = [[2018 Cavan Intermediate Football Championship]]\n| image                = \n| caption              = \n| irish                = \n| code                 = Gaelic football\n| founded              = 1915\n| abolished            = \n| region               = [[Cavan]], [[Ireland]]\n| trophy               = Tommy Gilroy Cup\n| teams                = 14\n| firstwin             = \n| title holders        = [[File:Colours of Armagh.svg|20px|border]] [[Laragh United GFC|Laragh United]]\n| currentordinal       = 2\n| super                = nd\n| most titles          = [[File:Colours of Dublin.svg|20px|border]] [[Lacken Celtic GFC|Lacken]]\n| mostordinal          = 4\n| sponsors             = Hotel Kilmore\n| tv                   = \n| motto                = \"The Future is Blue\"\n| website              = http://www.cavangaa.ie\n}}\nThe '''Cavan Intermediate Football Championship''' is an annual [[Gaelic Athletic Association]] competition between the middle-tier [[Gaelic football]] clubs organised by [[Cavan GAA]]. It was first competed for in 1915, before a lapse prior to being revived in 1966. The winners qualify to represent their county in the [[Ulster Intermediate Club Football Championship]] and in turn, go on to the [[All-Ireland Intermediate Club Football Championship]]. The current champions are [[Laragh United GFC|Laragh United]] who won in 2019.\n\n==Format==\n14 teams will contest the Hotel Kilmore Intermediate Football Championship.\n\nThe I.F.C. shall be run on a league basis up to the Quarter-Final stage and Knock-out thereafter. Each team will play 4 rounds in the league phase against different opponents with the fixtures decided by a random draw at the conclusion of each round. Placings in the league stage shall be decided in accordance with rule 6.21 of the GAA Official Guide 2016 as amended below:\n\n6.21 (4) If a Championship is partly organised on a League basis, the following Regulations shall apply: (a) League Results shall be credited as follows: 2 points for a win, and one for a draw. (b) If a Team is Disqualified or Retires during the course of a League Stage, its played games shall stand and its un-played games shall be awarded to the opposing teams. (c) As provided for in this Competition Regulation, when teams finish with equal points for Qualification for the Concluding Stages, or for Promotion or Relegation, the tie shall be decided by the following means and in the order specified: (i) Play-Off.\n\nThe top 8 teams in the league progress to the Quarter-Finals while the bottom 4 placed teams in the league enter a Relegation Playoff with 1 team to be relegated to the [[Cavan Junior Football Championship]]. The winner is promoted to the [[Cavan Senior Football Championship]]\n\n==Top winners==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n! style=\"background:blue; color:white; border:1px solid gold;\" |\n! style=\"background:blue; color:white; border:1px solid gold;\" | Team\n! style=\"background:blue; color:white; border:1px solid gold;\" | Wins\n! style=\"background:blue; color:white; border:1px solid gold;\" | Years won\n|-\n| 1\n| [[Lacken Celtic GFC|Lacken]]\n| 4\n| 1967, 1997, 2004, 2012\n|-\n| rowspan=6 |2\n| [[Drumalee GFC|Drumalee]] \n| 3\n| 1969, 2006, 2010\n|-\n| [[Ballinagh GAA|Ballinagh]]\n| 3\n| 1979, 1992, 2007\n|-\n| [[C\u00fachulainn's GFC (Cavan)|C\u00fachulainns]]\n| 3\n| 1987, 1993, 2005\n|-\n| [[Denn GFC|Denn]]\n| 3\n| 1988, 1990, 2003\n|-\n| [[Killeshandra GFC|Killeshandra]]\n| 3\n| 1986, 1991, 2013\n|-\n| Arva\n| 3\n| 1972, 1983, 2016\n|-\n| rowspan=12 | 3\n| [[Cornafean GAA|Cornafean]]\n| 2\n| 1915, 1916\n|-\n| [[Castlerahan GAA|Castlerahan]]\n| 2\n| 1966, 2001\n|-\n| [[Killygarry GAA|Killygarry]]\n| 2\n| 1970, 1998\n|-\n| [[Redhills GFC|Redhills]]\n| 2\n| 1973, 2008\n|-\n| Templeport\n| 2\n| 1977, 1995\n|-\n| Ballymachugh\n| 2\n| 1981, 1999\n|-\n| [[Drumgoon GFC|Drumgoon]]\n| 2\n| 2002, 2011\n|-\n| [[Cootehill Celtic GAA|Cootehill]]\n| 2\n| 1971, 2014\n|-\n| Ballyhaise\n| 2\n| 1968, 2015\n|-\n| Shercock\n| 2\n| 1984, 2017\n|-\n| [[Mullahoran GAA|Mullahoran]]\n| 2\n| 1978, 2018\n|-\n| [[Laragh United GFC|Laragh United]]\n| 2\n| 1994, 2019\n|-\n| rowspan=10 | 4\n| Maghera\n| 1\n| 1974\n|-\n| Virginia\n| 1\n| 1975\n|-\n| [[Kingscourt Stars GAA|Kingscourt Stars]]\n| 1\n| 1976\n|-\n| Munterconnaught\n| 1\n| 1980\n|-\n| Killinkere\n| 1\n| 1982\n|-\n| [[Gowna GFC|Gowna]]\n| 1\n| 1985\n|-\n| [[Bailieboro Shamrocks GAA|Bailieboro Shamrocks]]\n| 1\n| 1989\n|-\n| Belturbet\n| 1\n| 1996\n|-\n| Knockbride\n| 1\n| 2000\n|-\n| [[Lavey GFC (Cavan)|Lavey]]\n| 1\n| 2009\n|}\n\n==Roll of honour==\n{|class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! style=\"background:blue; color:white; border:1px solid gold;\" | Year\n! style=\"background:blue; color:white; border:1px solid gold;\" | Winner\n! style=\"background:blue; color:white; border:1px solid gold;\" | Opponent\n|-\n| 2019\n| [[Laragh United GFC|Laragh United]] 2-16\n| Belturbet 1-09\n|-\n| [[2018 Cavan Intermediate Football Championship|2018]]\n| [[Mullahoran GAA|Mullahoran]] 2-16\n| [[C\u00fachulainn's GFC (Cavan)|C\u00fachulainn's]] 0-08\n|-\n| 2017\n| Shercock 2-11\n| Ballyhaise 1-09\n|-\n| 2016\n| Arva 3-10, 0-11 (R)\n| Killinkere 1-16, 0-10 (R)\n|-\n| [[2015 Cavan Intermediate Football Championship|2015]]\n| Ballyhaise 2-13\n| Arva 1-14\n|-\n| [[2014 Cavan Intermediate Football Championship|2014]]\n| [[Cootehill Celtic GAA|Cootehill]] 3-11\n| Ballyhaise 0-08\n|-\n| [[2013 Cavan Intermediate Football Championship|2013]]\n| [[Killeshandra GFC|Killeshandra]] 1-10\n| Shercock 1-08\n|-\n| 2012\n| [[Lacken Celtic GFC|Lacken]] 3-10\n| [[Cootehill Celtic GAA|Cootehill]] 1-09\n|-\n| 2011\n| [[Drumgoon GFC|Drumgoon]] 0-11\n| [[Crosserlough GFC|Crosserlough]] 1-07\n|-\n| 2010\n| [[Drumalee GFC|Drumalee]] 1-11\n| Drumlane 0-08\n|-\n| 2009\n| [[Lavey GFC (Cavan)|Lavey]] 